  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN197.1-kilavi">piriviṭai vēṟupaṭṭa talaimakaḷait tōḻi <app><lem>vaṟpuṟuttiyatu</lem><rdg wit="#C9v #RK">vaṟpurīiyatu</rdg></app>.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">How the confidante consoled HER who had undergone changes in the time of separation.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="AN197.1">
        <l><anchor n="1"/>māmalar vaṇṇa miḻanta kaṇṇum</l>
        <l>pūneki ḻaṇaiyiṟ cāaya tōḷu</l>
        <l>naṉṉar mākkaḷ viḻaivaṉa rāynta</l>
        <l>toṉṉala miḻanta tuyaramō ṭeṉṉatūu</l>
        <l>miṉaiyal vāḻi tōḻi muṉaiyeḻa</l>
        <l>muṉṉuva rōṭṭiya muraṇmiku tiruviṉ</l>
        <l>māmiku tāṉaik kaṇ<supplied>ṇa ṉe</supplied>ḻiṉi</l>
        <l>tēmutu kuṉṟa miṟantaṉa rāyiṉu</l>
        <l>nīṭalar yāḻaniṉ ṉiraivaḷai nekiḻat</l>
        <l>tōṭāḻ piruḷiya kuvaiyiruṅ kūntaṉ</l>
        <l>maṭavōṭ ṭaḻīiya viṟalōṉ mārpiṟ</l>
        <l>puṉṟalaip putalva ṉūrpiḻin tāṅkuk</l>
        <l>kaṭuñcūṉ maṭappiṭi taḻīiya veṇkōṭ</l>
        <l>ṭiṉañcāl vēḻaṅ kaṉṟūr piḻitarap</l>
        <l>paḷḷi koḷḷum paṉiccura nīnti</l>
        <l>yoḷḷiṇark koṉṟai yōṅkumalai yattam</l>
        <l>viṉaivali yuṟūu neñcamō</l>
        <l>ṭiṉaiya rākinap pi<supplied>ri</supplied>ntici ṉōrē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>With misery as the old beauty is lost (4a-c)</l>
        <l>that was chosen by the good people who are desirous (3)</l>
        <l>of [your] eyes that [now] have lost the colour of dark blossoms (1)</l>
        <l>and [your] shoulders that [now] are emaciated on the bed on which flowers come loose, (2)</l>
        <l>don’t despair one bit, friend. (4d-5c)</l>
        <l>Even if he has gone to traverse the old honey hill (8a-c)</l>
        <l>of Kaṇṇaṉ Eḻiṉi, with an army abounding in horses, (7)</l>
        <l>with brilliance, abounding in enmity that chases away those who approach him</l>
        <l rend="indent8">when the frontier rises, (5df.)</l>
        <l>he will not delay so that your bangles in a row become loose, (9)</l>
        <l>– he who, (17d)</l>
        <l>crossing the chilly dew, where the elephant bull worthy of [its] herd</l>
        <l>takes rest while [its] calf climbs [it and] glides down], (14f.)</l>
        <l>with white tusks that embrace [its] youthful cow in high pregnancy, (13)</l>
        <l>as if a son with ruddy head were to climb up [and] glide down (12)</l>
        <l>the chest of a victorious man who embraces [his] youthful [wife] (11)</l>
        <l>with dark tresses in a mass that is dark and falling down on [her] shoulders, (10)</l>
        <l rend="indent8">parted from us, being like that, (17)</l>
        <l>with a heart that felt strength for work, (16)</l>
        <l>on the road of high mountains with bright-clustered kino trees. (15)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>

